HEADWORD: Nidorous
<hw>Ni"dor*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nidorosus</ets> steaming, reeking: cf. F. <ets>nidoreux</ets>. See
<er>Nidor</er>.]</ety> <def>Resembling the smell or taste of roast meat,
or of corrupt animal matter.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

